On Tue, 13 Mar 2012, Scott Busby wrote:

> The rubber thing is called the steering coupler. I just replaced mine,
> as well as the whole steering box.

I've found it much easier to replace the coupler which I do every 10 years 
or when it has cracks by going from the top and just sliding the steering 
column up an inch or so, doesn't take much to slide the old one out and 
the new one in. then four bolts to hold it.

